h1801.definition: a primitive root; to spring; leap.

h1802.definition: a primitive root (compare {{h1809}}); properly, to dangle, i.e. to let down a bucket (for drawing out water); figuratively, to deliver; draw (out), × enough, lift up.

h1803.definition: from {{h1802}}; properly, something dangling, i.e. a loose thread or hair; figuratively, indigent; hair, pining sickness, poor(-est sort).

h1804.definition: a primitive root; to roil water; trouble.

h1805.definition: or דֳּלִי; from {{h1802}}; a pail or jar (for drawing water); bucket.

h1806.definition: or (prolonged) דְּלָיָהוּxlit Dᵉlâyâhhûw corrected to Dᵉlâyâhûw; from {{h1802}} and {{h3050}}; Jah has delivered; Delajah, the name of five Israelites; Dalaiah, Delaiah.

h1807.definition: from {{h1809}}; languishing; Delilah, a Philistine woman; Delilah.

h1808.definition: from {{h1802}}; something dangling, i.e. a bough; branch.

h1809.definition: a primitive root (compare {{h1802}}); to slacken or be feeble; figuratively, to be oppressed; bring low, dry up, be emptied, be not equal, fail, be impoverished, be made thin.

h1810.definition: of uncertain derivation; Dilan, a place in Palestine; Dilean.

h1811.definition: a primitive root; to drip; by implication, to weep; drop through, melt, pour out.

h1813.definition: from {{h1811}}; dripping; Dalphon, a son of Haman; Dalphon.

h1814.definition: a primitive root; to flame (literally or figuratively); burning, chase, inflame, kindle, persecute(-or), pursue hotly.

h1817.definition: from {{h1802}}; something swinging, i.e. the valve of a door; door (two-leaved), gate, leaf, lid. (Psalm 141:3).

h1818.definition: from {{h1826}} (compare {{h119}}); blood (as that which when shed causes death) of man or an animal; by analogy, the juice of the grape; figuratively (especially in the plural) bloodshed (i.e. drops of blood); blood(-y, -guiltiness, (-thirsty),   innocent.

h1819.definition: a primitive root; to compare; by implication, to resemble, liken, consider; compare, devise, (be) like(-n), mean, think, use similitudes.

h1820.definition: a primitive root; to be dumb or silent; hence, to fail or perish; trans. to destroy; cease, be cut down (off), destroy, be brought to silence, be undone, × utterly.

h1821.definition: (Aramaic) corresponding to {{h1819}}; to resemble; be like.

h1823.definition: from {{h1819}}; resemblance; concretely, model, shape; adverbially, like; fashion, like (-ness, as), manner, similitude.

h1824.definition: or דֳּמִי; from {{h1820}}; quiet; cutting off, rest, silence.

h1826.definition: a primitive root (compare {{h1724}}, {{h1820}}); to be dumb; by implication, to be astonished, to stop; also to perish; cease, be cut down (off), forbear, hold peace, quiet self, rest, be silent, keep (put to) silence, be (stand) still, tarry, wait.

h1827.definition: feminine from {{h1826}}; quiet; calm, silence, still.

h1829.definition: feminine from the same as {{h1828}}; a dung-heap; Dimnah, a place in Palestine; Dimnah.

h1830.definition: a primitive root; to weep; × sore, weep.

h1831.definition: from {{h1830}}; a tear; figuratively, juice; liquor.

h1833.definition: by orthographical variation from {{h1834}}; damask (as a fabric of Damascus); in Damascus.

h1834.definition: or דּוּמֶשֶׂק; or דַּרְמֶשֶׂק; of foreign origin; Damascus, a city of Syria; Damascus.

h1835.definition: from {{h1777}}; judge; Dan, one of the sons of Jacob; also the tribe descended from him, and its territory; likewise a place in Palestine colonized by them; Daniel

h1836.definition: (Aramaic) an orthographical variation of {{h1791}}; this; (afore-) time,   after this manner, here (-after), one...another, such, there(-fore), these, this (matter),   thus, where(-fore), which.

h1837.definition: of uncertain derivation; Dannah, a place in Palestine; Dannah.

h1838.definition: of uncertain derivation; Dinhabah, an Edomitish town; Dinhaban.

h1839.definition: patronymically from {{h1835}}; a Danite (often collectively) or descendants (or inhabitants) of Dan; Danites, of Daniel

h1840.definition: in Ezekiel it is; דָּנִאֵל; from {{h1835}} and {{h410}}; judge of God; Daniel or Danijel, the name of two Israelites; Daniel.

h1841.definition: (Aramaic) corresponding to {{h1840}}; Danijel, the Hebrew prophet; Daniel.

h1842.definition: from {{h1835}} and (apparently) {{h3282}}; judge of purpose; Dan-Jaan, a place in Palestine; Dan-jaan.

h1845.definition: from {{h3045}} and {{h410}}; known of God; Deuel, an Israelite; Deuel.

h1846.definition: a primitive root; to be extinguished; figuratively, to expire or be dried up; be extinct, consumed, put out, quenched.

h1847.definition: from {{h3045}}; knowledge; cunning, (ig-) norantly, know(-ledge), (un-) awares (wittingly).

h1848.definition: from an unused root (meaning to push over); a stumbling-block; slanderest.

h1849.definition: a primitive root; to knock; by analogy, to press severely; beat, knock, overdrive.

h1850.definition: from {{h1849}}; a knock; Dophkah, a place in the Desert; Dophkah.

h1851.definition: from {{h1854}}; crushed, i.e. (by implication) small or thin; dwarf, lean(-fleshed), very little thing, small, thin.

h1852.definition: from {{h1854}}; something crumbling, i.e. fine (as a thin cloth); curtain.

h1853.definition: of foreign origin; Diklah, a region of Arabia; Diklah.

h1854.definition: a primitive root (compare {{h1915}}); to crush (or intransitively) crumble; beat in pieces (small), bruise, make dust, (into) × powder, (be, very) small, stamp (small).

h1855.definition: (Aramaic) corresponding to {{h1854}}; to crumble or (trans.) crush; break to pieces.

h1856.definition: a primitive root; to stab; by analogy, to starve; figuratively, to revile; pierce, strike (thrust) through, wound.

h1857.definition: from {{h1856}}; a stab; Deker, an Israelite; Dekar.

h1858.definition: apparently from the same as {{h1865}}; properly, a pearl (from its sheen as rapidly turned); by analogy, pearl-stone, i.e. mother-of-pearl or alabaster; × white.

h1860.definition: or דֵּרָאוֹן; from an unused root (meaning to repulse); an object of aversion; abhorring, contempt.

h1861.definition: (also dor-bawn'); of uncertain derivation; a goad; goad.

h1862.definition: apparently from {{h1858}} and {{h1843}}; pearl of knowledge; Darda, an Israelite; Darda.

h1863.definition: of uncertain derivation; a thorn; thistle.

h1864.definition: of uncertain derivation; the south; poet. the south wind; south.

h1865.definition: from an unused root (meaning to move rapidly); freedom; hence, spontaneity of outflow, and so clear; liberty, pure.

h1866.definition: the same as {{h1865}}, applied to a bird; the swift, a kind of swallow; swallow.

h1867.definition: of Persian origin; Darejavesh, a title (rather than name) of several Persian kings; Darius.

h1869.definition: a primitive root; to tread; by implication, to walk; also to string a bow (by treading on it in bending); archer, bend, come, draw, go (over), guide, lead (forth), thresh, tread (down), walk.

h1870.definition: from {{h1869}}; a road (as trodden); figuratively, a course of life or mode of action, often adverb; along, away, because of,   by, conversation, custom, (east-) ward, journey, manner, passenger, through, toward, (high-) (path-) way(-side), whither(-soever).

h1871.definition: of Persian origin; a 'drachma', or coin; dram.

h1873.definition: probably a contraction from {{h1862}}; Dara, an Israelite; Dara.

h1874.definition: of uncertain derivation; Darkon, one of 'Solomon's servants'; Darkon.

h1875.definition: a primitive root; properly, to tread or frequent; usually to follow (for pursuit or search); by implication, to seek or ask; specifically to worship; ask, × at all, care for, × diligently, inquire, make inquisition, (necro-) mancer, question, require, search, seek (for, out), × surely.

h1876.definition: a primitive root; to sprout; bring forth, spring.

h1877.definition: from {{h1876}}; a sprout; by analogy, grass; (tender) grass, green, (tender) herb.

h1878.definition: a primitive root; also denominatively (from {{h1880}}); to be fat; transitively, to fatten (or regard as fat); specifically to anoint; figuratively, to satisfy; to remove (fat) ashes (of sacrifices); accept, anoint, take away the (receive) ashes (from), make (wax) fat.

h1879.definition: from {{h1878}}; fat; figuratively, rich, fertile; fat.

h1880.definition: from {{h1878}}; the fat; abstractly fatness, i.e. (figuratively) abundance; specifically the (fatty) ashes of sacrifices; ashes, fatness.

h1881.definition: of uncertain (perhaps foreign) derivation; a royal edict or statute; commandment, commission, decree, law, manner.

h1884.definition: (Aramaic) of Persian origin; meaning one skilled in law; a judge; counsellor.

h1885.definition: of uncertain derivation; Dathan, an Israelite; Dathan.

h1886.definition: or (Aramaic dual) דֹּתַיִן; (Genesis 37:17), of uncertain derivation; Dothan, a place in Palestine; Dothan. h

h1887.definition: a primitive particle; lo!; behold, lo.

h1888.definition: (Aramaic) or הָא; (Aramaic), corresponding to {{h1887}}; even, lo.

h1889.definition: from {{h1887}} and {{h253}}; aha!; ah, aha, ha.

h1890.definition: by reduplication from {{h3051}}; gift (in sacrifice), i.e. holocaust; offering.

h1891.definition: a primitive root; to be vain in act, word, or expectation; specifically to lead astray; be (become, make) vain.

h1892.definition: or (rarely in the abs.) הֲבֵל; from {{h1891}}; emptiness or vanity; figuratively, something transitory and unsatisfactory; often used as an adverb; × altogether, vain, vanity.

h1893.definition: the same as {{h1892}}; Hebel, the son of Adam; Abel.

h1894.definition: only in plural, from an unused root meaning to be hard; ebony; ebony.

h1895.definition: a primitive root of uncertain (perhaps foreign) derivation; to be a horoscopist; (astro-) loger.

h1896.definition: or (by permutation) הֵגַי; probably of Persian origin; Hege or Hegai, a eunuch of Xerxes; Hegai, Hege.

h1897.definition: a primitive root (compare {{h1901}}); to murmur (in pleasure or anger); by implication, to ponder; imagine, meditate, mourn, mutter, roar, × sore, speak, study, talk, utter.

h1898.definition: a primitive root; to remove; stay, stay away.

h1899.definition: from {{h1897}}; a muttering (in sighing, thought, or as thunder); mourning, sound, tale.
